Muhammad Sanusi 11 was on Monday dethroned as Emir of Kano over alleged violation of the traditions, customs and practices of the ancient city by Kano State Government. He was replaced by his cousin, Emir Aminu Ado Bayero, who was the Emir of Bichi, until his elevation. While he lasted as Emir, Sanusi was not only visible but also outspoken. Here are five things to recall about the flamboyant exiled traditional ruler: In 2014, President Goodluck Jonathan suspended him after raising the alarm on the US$20 billion NNPC scandal. The Nation